JOHANNESBURG – A shocking video of a South African woman being shoved down a flight of stairs in Amsterdam, is making the rounds on social media. The video was posted on Facebook by Steve Nkumbi, captioned "When racism is unapologetically visible. I was assaulted, verbally abused and physically abused by a white Man! This happened to me this morning! I am in agony. Comrades, Aluta continua!" Later South African photographer Zanele Muholi posted the video on Instagram, describing it as racist incidence. In the video, her friend is pushed down the stairs, allegedly by an Airbnb owner, at the place they were staying. The attack happened after what appears to be a disagreement between the women and owner. Airbnb has responded to the incident with outrage. READ - Airbnb slams incident where SA woman is pushed down stairs eNCA